# 7. みんなで夢を

Tsukasa: Alright, we're just about finished cleaning the stage, so let's start heading home.
Emu: Okay! Get home safe, you guys!
Rui: Are you not walking with us to the main gate, Emu?
Emu: Not today! I just got a message from my brothers... They're coming here to meet me in a bit!
Tsukasa: I see... Then, we'll see you tomorrow.
Nene: Um, Emu...?
Nene: The taiyaki place we always go to started selling ones with a strawberry milk flavored filling yesterday. Let's go grab some tomorrow.
Emu: Okay!
Tsukasa: Well then, farewell!
Emu: *Stretch* We had another really fun practice today! Everyone sounded so excited about our show!
Emu: Probably because of the one Miku and the others put on for us, huh?
Emu: It was so good...
Emu: KAITO and the others did a wonderhoy job as the troupe members.
Emu: And they even changed the ending.
Emu: They went their separate ways, but all came back together...
Emu: Oh no...
Emu: What do I do...?
Emu: They won't stop...
Emu: I'm Emu Otori! Welcome to the fantastic Wonder Stage, a place filled with lots of smiles!
Emu: Let's put on some incredible shows together, Tsukasa!
Tsukasa: Huh...? Wh-Whaaaaaat?
Tsukasa: What the heck is going on?!
Tsukasa: Say hello to our new stage director!
Emu: Wow! You're the performer from yesterday! Welcome, and wonderhoy☆
Rui: Hmm... I didn't know about this stage. It's old, but well-maintained.
Rui: You must be the other cast member Tsukasa mentioned. I'm Rui Kamishiro. Nice to meet you.
Emu: Little Robot, do you have a name?
Robot: A name... Um...
Rui: Come to think of it, we haven't named the robot. Could you tell them your name instead this time?
Robot: ... Nene Kusanagi.
Emu: *Sob*
Emu: *Sob*
Tsukasa: The show Miku and the others put on for us today was extraordinary.
Rui: Yes, it certainly was. Their thoughtfulness really knows no bounds.
Rui: We may be going our separate ways now, but we can still be together again someday... At least, that's the message I heard.
Nene: Yeah, me too...
Nene: I feel a lot better about what's ahead after seeing their show.
Nene: Still...
Nene: Do you think Emu's gonna be okay...?
Nene: She had her usual smile during practice...
Nene: But she's also able to keep smiling for someone else's sake. Even when she's not feeling all that great...
Tsukasa: Yes, you're right... I wish there were something we could do for her...
Tsukasa: But this time around...
Rui: ...
Nene: Yeah...
Nene: But I still wanna do as much stuff as I can with her. Like going home together, messaging each other and...
Nene: Wait...
Rui: Hm? What's wrong?
Nene: Oh, um... I just remembered that I left my phone in the changing room...
Tsukasa: What? Then, you need to go get it!
Rui: Fortunately, we're still not very far from the Wonder Stage. Shall we head back together?
Nene: O-Okay. Sorry, you guys. And thanks...
Nene: Just gimme a sec. I'll be right back.
Tsukasa: Of course. Feel free to take your time since you're moving in the dark.
Rui: Did you hear something just now...?
Tsukasa: Hm? Hear what...?
Tsukasa: ...! Hey, that looks like...!
Tsukasa: Is she...crying...?
Nene: Emu...
Rui: Nene...!
Emu: *Sob*
Nene: Emu!
Emu: ...?! N-Nene?! What are you doing here...?!
Nene: Emu, your face...
Emu: Huh? No, I...! I wasn't crying! My eyes are just hurting because I didn't get enough sleep...
Nene: You big dummy...!!!
Nene: Why are you crying all by yourself?!
Nene: If you're gonna cry... Then cry when we're here!
Nene: Don't you remember what I said?! What Tsukasa said?! What Rui said?! We want to do everything we can to make sure you keep smiling!
Nene: I know... Unlike all those other times, our hands are tied for this one...
Nene: But if you feel sad, we should be sharing that feeling together!
Nene: At least let us do that...!
Emu: Nene...
Emu: ...
Emu: But...! But...!
Emu: I want us to be smiling when we say goodbye to each other!
Emu: I want you guys to feel happy about setting out into the world...
Emu: I don't want those smiles of yours to fade away...!
Nene: ...
Tsukasa: Tenma, written as “soaring pegasus”!
Emu, Nene & Rui: ?!
Tsukasa: Tsukasa, meaning to govern!
Tsukasa: I am Tsukasa Tenma, the soaring pegasus born to rule the showbiz world!
Tsukasa: As a future star, and as the troupe leader of Wonderlands×Showtime, I must interject!
Tsukasa: Wanting to part ways while smiling— I understand that feeling well!
Nene: Tsukasa...
Tsukasa: We've always been surrounded by smiles and laughter.
Tsukasa: The audience is an obvious example, but more to the point...
Tsukasa: Whenever Rui thinks up a new stunt or special effect, whenever Nene sings, whenever you talk about your big dreams, Emu...
Tsukasa: We always find ourselves smiling and laughing. We all want each other to be happy.
Tsukasa: Which is why... I understand your desire for us to keep smiling to the very end.
Emu: ...
Tsukasa: However...
Tsukasa: We don't have to right now, do we...?
Emu: What...?
Tsukasa: Us going our separate ways after having so much fun together is painful to say the least.
Tsukasa: My heart aches so much...
Rui: Tsukasa...
Tsukasa: So, I am allowing us to all do the same!
Tsukasa: Let us take this opportunity to cry together...!!!
Rui: You already are...
Tsukasa: Yes, didn't you hear what I just said! Now is our chance to cry together!
Nene: *Sigh* Why are you making it into some rule...? I was trying to have a serious conversation...
Nene: Now it all just feels stupid...
Emu: Hehe... Your face is so messy now, Tsukasa...
Emu: It looks all funny...
Tsukasa: Look who's talking, Emu! Your face has turned into a balled up tissue!
Emu: That makes yours a crumpled up piece of newspaper...!
Rui: Hehe. This is so strange... We're all crying, but laughing at the same time...
Rui: This situation captures us so well...
Nene: It does...
Tsukasa: Emu...
Tsukasa: Thank you for asking me to join you that time.
Tsukasa: You're the reason I've been able to make such wonderful friends, and pursue my dream.
Tsukasa: I can't thank you enough...
Emu: ... *Sob*
Emu: *Cry*
???: Emu, are you there...?
???: No, wait...
???: Hm? Why?
???: It looks like they're somewhat preoccupied...
Shosuke: I regret not doing this a little sooner...
Shosuke: Hey, all of you! Sorry, but we need to talk!
Tsukasa: Huh?! Wh-What's going on?!
Emu: Shosuke...?!
Keisuke: We were planning to speak with Emu first...
Keisuke: But since you're all together, we'll say it all right here.
Rui: Say it all...? What is it?
Shosuke: This is about what matters the most to all of you.
Keisuke: As Emu's brothers, we want to respect her wishes.
Keisuke: Regardless of whether or not she decided to stay, we planned to support her choice.
Shosuke: However...
Shosuke: Hearing her decision caused us to begin doubting ourselves.
Shosuke: We weren't sure if this would be what's best for her. A lot of things started going through our minds, including whether we'd regret this down the road...
Shosuke: And in the end, we don't believe this is what's best.
Tsukasa: It's not...?
Nene: Wait, what do you mean...?
Keisuke: Go.
Emu: What...?
Keisuke: We understand your wish to protect Phoenix Wonderland and keep it filled with smiles.
Keisuke: Obviously, that makes us happy as the operators of this park, and your passion would make you a valuable member of our team.
Keisuke: But you're still just a high schooler...
Emu: ...!
Keisuke: You should be seeing what the outside world has to offer.
Keisuke: The time you have now... What you experience during your youth will surely benefit you down the road in terms of both your dream and your life as a whole.
Keisuke: And of course... It will help Phoenix Wonderland in the future.
Emu: But...
Shosuke: Think about this, Emu.
Shosuke: Before we became this park's operators, we traveled to more places than you can imagine.
Shosuke: In particular, we got ourselves introduced to the world of show business. And not just theatre. We went around learning as much as we could about the film and animation industries.
Shosuke: I wouldn't say that all of what we saw is helping us with our current jobs. However, I can say that it made us who we are now as professionals...
Emu: Really...?
Shosuke: Yes, really. And can you guess who suggested that we do that...?
Shosuke: It was Grandpa.
Emu: ...!
Rakunosuke: And once what you've seen here has made you smile, you should take a look at the world around you...
Rakunosuke: Unfortunately, unlike what you see on stage, it's not all full of smiles and happiness.
Rakunosuke: But I'm sure what you witness will become the fuel that drives you.
Emu: Oh...
Shosuke: If you truly wish to protect this place... Go out and expand your horizons, and then return.
Shosuke: Until then, we'll keep an eye on Phoenix Wonderland for you.
Shosuke: Because your dream has also become our dream.
Emu: Shosuke...
Keisuke: Kamishiro.
Rui: Y-Yes...?!
Keisuke: Thank you for doing your best to not interfere with our business. That was very considerate of you.
Keisuke: However, this is also an important time for you. There's no need for you to shape your thoughts based on our needs...
Rui: ...!
Keisuke: We'll do everything in our power to make sure this park keeps growing. To make sure Phoenix Wonderland stays filled with smiles.
Keisuke: And if you still genuinely wish to perform here again someday...
Keisuke: You'll be more than welcome. We promise to reward you handsomely.
Rui: ...!
Rui: Are you sure about this...?
Keisuke: Yes. This is what we've decided.
Rui: Thank you very much!
Tsukasa & Nene: Thank you very much!
Tsukasa: Won't you join us, Emu?
Tsukasa: As a humble actor, I am in no position to make any claims regarding what your brothers just said.
Tsukasa: All I have to say is...that I want to keep doing shows with you.
Tsukasa: I mean that...
Emu: ...
Rui: Emu... Please allow me to ask you again.
Rui: I truly wish to keep doing shows with this troupe. I mean every word of that.
Rui: If there's a way for you to pursue your dream as we pursue ours, won't you be willing to reconsider our invitation...?
Nene: He's right, Emu...!
Nene: Come with us!
Emu: I...
Emu: I don't ever want to break the promise I made to Grandpa...
Emu: But... If there's a way that lets me protect this park and go with you guys...
Emu: I...!
Keisuke: Go, Emu.
Keisuke: We'll be eagerly awaiting your return.
Emu: Okay...!!!
Emu: I'm gonna go with them!
Emu: I'm gonna go out there and learn as much as I can! And I'm gonna find a way to fill this park with even more smiles!
Nene: Emu...!!!
Emu: I'm really sorry, everyone... I didn't mean to make you all worry so much about me...
Nene: *Sigh* What are you saying? There's no need for you to apologize to us.
Tsukasa: She's right! “Sorry” isn't what we want to hear right now!
Rui: Yes, I agree.
Emu: Thanks, you guys!
Emu: Thanks for letting me come with you!
